From Robert Loper Subject Re SHO and SC In article James Callison writes In article David Hwang writes In article wrat wharfie writes In article Chris Silvester writes Why anyone would order an SHO with an automatic transmission is beyond me if you can't handle a stick you should stick with a regular Taurus and leave the SHO to real That is not to say that there aren't real drivers who can't use the stick eg disabled persons but they aren't in any position to use an SHO I would be willing to bet that if we removed the automatic transmissions from all performance type cars like the Mustangs Camaros and the like we'd cut down on the number of accidents each Autos are fine for sedate little sedans but they have no business in performance cars James I have to disagree with I have a with a and a speed auto w overdrive and it is really better that Chevy autos are reknowned for their long life and ability to handle copious amount of I live in the Dallas area and a manual would be much harder to drive in the traffic Now if I still lived out in the sticks like I used to a manual would be more Safety wise an auto is less would hate to have to be shifting gears while I was trying to ease into traffic in the freeways Performance wise I can hold my own against any stock Mustang or Camaro w a five All of this Robert Loper Infinity is a notion best contemplated ROBERTLL in a warm Texas Instruments My opinions are my own not TI'